VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT (?i)\bSELECT\s+\*?\s+FROM\s+[^\s]+\s+(WHERE|ORDER BY)\b.*
WHEN EXPR PRESENT:(\.\s*\$|\$_(GET|POST|REQUEST|COOKIE)|sprintf\s*\(|format\s*\() && MISSING:prepare\s*\(|bind_param|bindValue|bindParam|PDO::prepare
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects non-parameterized SELECT statements with WHERE or ORDER BY clauses in SQL queries, which may be vulnerable to SQL injection if user input is not handled securely.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for SQL Query: Non-parameterized SELECT Statements with WHERE or ORDER BY.
